metadata.name: Sheep Clones 1/4000
metadata.description:
In a secret laboratory deep in the mountains, a group of scientists were working on an experiment to clone sheep. However, their experiment took a dark turn when one of the clones became infected with a virus. The virus transformed the sheep into a zombie-like creature, with glowing eyes and a fierce hunger for flesh.

The virus quickly spread throughout the laboratory, infecting all of the sheep clones. The scientists tried to contain the virus, but it was too late. The sheep clones had broken out of their pens and were now running rampant through the facility, infecting everything in their path.

As the virus continued to spread, the sheep clones began to mutate, growing larger and more aggressive with each passing day. They became stronger and more resilient, making them nearly impossible to kill.

The situation quickly became dire as the sheep clones spread beyond the laboratory. The world was plunged into chaos as the zombie sheep clones ravaged the countryside, leaving destruction in their wake.
